rComments: He's honestly alright. Nothing is a surprise on his tests, just go to lecture and listen. This class is also much better than BIO203, much more interesting even if you despise plants. Labs are worth a lot and are easy to ace, and no final exam. I took it for a BIO credit, not for interest, and managed to get a 75.
he likes to repeatedly use the terms "roots and shoots" as well as relating everything possible to Germany (for example: leaves change color in the fall, thats the same time as oktoberfest... )

Lectures: Read off the slides = boring, did not interact with the class, since he is passionate about plant physiology, he should find better ways to express that, e.g. via making the student learning experience alot better. It was horrible, the textbook did a better job at entertaining me.
He is a good lecturer, but lectures were word for word from the textbook so no point in attending.
amazing prof, very passionate about what he's teaching. makes plants seem interesting. really helpful and approachable as well.

Boring prof. Has a thick German Accent that is hard to understand and just directly reads off the lecture slides with little enthusiasm. But apparently of lot of girls seem to think he is good-looking.
